# ‚úÖ **Installation Requirements (Add to README)**

````md
## ‚úÖ Installation Requirements

Before running the Face Attendance System, ensure your system meets these requirements:

---

### üñ•Ô∏è **System Requirements**

| Component | Minimum Requirement |
|----------|----------------------|
| OS | Windows / macOS / Linux |
| RAM | 4GB+ (8GB recommended) |
| Node.js | v18 or later |
| npm | v9 or later |
| Expo CLI | Latest |
| Android Studio (optional) | For emulator builds |
| JDK | JDK 17 (if using prebuild/EAS Android) |

---

### üì¶ **Required Global Tools**

Install Node.js (if not installed):  
https://nodejs.org/

Install Expo CLI:

```sh
npm install -g expo-cli
````

Install EAS CLI:

```sh
npm install -g eas-cli
```

---

### üì± **Expo Modules Used**

Install all required dependencies:

```sh
npm install expo-camera
npm install expo-face-detector
npm install expo-permissions
npm install expo-file-system
npm install expo-constants
```

Or install all at once:

```sh
npm install expo-camera expo-face-detector expo-permissions expo-file-system expo-constants
```

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è **Project Dependencies**

Install project packages:

```sh
npm install
```

If you have errors:

```sh
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
```

---

### üîß **Android Build Requirements**

If you want to use **EAS Build or local Android build**:

Install:

* **Android Studio**
* **Android SDK 34+**
* **Platform Tools (ADB)**
* **JDK 17**

Set environment variables (Windows):

```sh
setx JAVA_HOME "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-17"
setx ANDROID_HOME "%LOCALAPPDATA%\Android\Sdk"
```

---

### üì∑ **Permissions Required**

The app needs:

```md
Camera Access  
File System Access (for logs)  
Internet Access (for syncing)
```

Expo auto-handles permissions.

---

### üßπ Optional Cleanup

If prebuild breaks:

```sh
npx expo prebuild --clean
```

If EAS build issues:

```sh
eas clean --all
```

